        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 25 at 5:17PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 517 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Jim R Miller Park, or
near Marietta, moving west at 10 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Marietta, Smyrna, Kennesaw, Powder Springs, Austell, Hiram, Fair
Oaks, Due West, Lost Mountain Park, New Hope, and Jim R Miller Park.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
